Title: Scientific American Molecular Neurology (scientific American Introduction To Molecular Medicine)
Author: জোসেফ বি. মার্টিন
Summary: Advances in molecular biology have allowed the progress made over the past decade in identifying genes causing neurologic disorders. This book, by a team of leading experts in the field, discusses recent discoveries, many of which still await a therapeutic application. Neurologists, psychiatrists, internists and others wishing to broaden their understanding of the basic pathogenic mechanisms underlying neurologic disease will value this book.
